            , we met the prisoner; he sold the axe to Bowbrick, this is the axe, and the prisoner<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181502150016"></xptr>is the man.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I gave a shilling for the axe, at Hounslow, and a pint of beer for the stone.</p>
